<amendatorysection amended="yes" chaptername="Revenue And Taxation" id="id445" statutenumber="77-1827"><bookinfo>Reissue Revised Statutes of Nebraska</bookinfo><statuteno>77-1827</statuteno><catchline id="id448">Real property
taxes; redemption; persons with intellectual
disability or mental disorder; time permitted.</catchline><para>The real property of persons with an intellectual disability or a mental disorder
so sold, or any interest they may have in real property sold for taxes, may
be redeemed at any time within five years after such sale.</para>
